<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 9:16PM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Somervell
and northwestern Bosque Counties through 945 PM CDT...
At 916 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Iredell, or 22 miles northwest of Clifton, moving northeast at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Glen Rose, Meridian, Iredell, Walnut Springs and Morgan.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
central Texas.</instruction>
